Installation instructions for WYSIWYG extension 1.4
---------------------------------------------------

Install instructions for the latest version of the WYSIWYG Extension are also online:

 http://smwforum.ontoprise.com/smwforum/index.php/Help:Installing_the_WYSIWYG_extension
 
For the full manual of the Semantic Rules Extension have a look at:

 http://smwforum.ontoprise.com/smwforum/index.php/Help:WYSIWYG_Extension_1.4
 

Requirements: 
=============

	MediaWiki 1.16.0 see installation guide: http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Installation_guide)

Installation:
=============

(1) Extract the zip-file (wysiwyg-1.4.0_0.zip)
(2) Copy the folder wysiwyg-1.4.0_0\extensions\WYSIWYG into the folder ..\htdocs\mediawiki\extensions
(3) Add the following line to your LocalSettings.php to initialize the extension
    require_once("$IP/extensions/WYSIWYG/WYSIWYG.php");
(4) Define the group rights, the easiest is to grant all users access:
    $wgGroupPermissions['*']['wysiwyg']=true;
    
    or only for registeres users:
    $wgGroupPermissions['registered_users']['wysiwyg']=true;
    

Now the WYSIWYG Extension is installed and ready to use.